# SuperGit Project

VS Code extension for a Git commit graph, branch tracking, and branch history webview.

## Source of truth

- Product behavior/UI: **`.cursor/rules/supergit-*.mdc`** (this file + scoped rules below). Do not rely on deleted `Design/` mockups.
- Commit graph: `supergit-commit-graph.mdc`
- Webview/CSP/panel: `supergit-webview.mdc`
- Branch history: `supergit-branch-history.mdc`
- Refresh/coalescing/cache: `supergit-refresh-coordination.mdc`
- Assets: `assets/icon.png` (package/panel icon), `assets/logo.png` (webview logo)

## Design goals

- Dark VS Code-native webview; dense, operational, tool-like UI (not a landing page)
- Commit graph tab, branch tracking tab, **branch history tab**, multi-remote visibility, guarded Git actions
- Stable dimensions for graph lanes, sidebars, toolbar, rows, status areas
- Do not replace real UI with explanatory placeholder text
- Branch tracking actions must be **contextual**: after selection, show ahead/behind/synced/diverged/no-upstream/**remote-only** and enable/highlight only sensible push/pull/upstream actions

